comments: Biyombo (CHA) sets the pick in Okogie's (MIN) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Beasley (MIN) moves laterally into Washington's (CHA) path at the end of the drive but the contact is marginal and does not affect his ability to pass.
Russell (MIN) makes contact with Bridges's (CHA) body during his shooting motion that affects his jump shot attempt.
Monk (CHA) cleanly blocks Beasley's (DEN) driving shot attempt.
Monk (CHA) makes marginal contact with Hernangomez's (MIN) body before blocking the shot attempt near the rim.

Hernangomez (MIN) makes marginal contact with Bridges' (CHA) head during the loose ball. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Monk (CHA) sets the pick in Hernangomez's (MIN) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Washington (CHA) cleanly dislodges the ball from Russell (MIN) on the perimeter.
Russell (MIN) places a marginal hand to Graham's (CHA) side on the perimeter.
Beasley (MIN) makes clean contact with the ball as he defends the pass to Monk (CHA) near midcourt.
Okogie (MIN) and Graham (CHA) briefly engage and separate during the inbound.
Okogie (MIN) commits a take foul on Graham (CHA).
Bridges (CHA) cleanly blocks Russell's (MIN) jump shot attempt.
Johnson (MIN) sets the screen in Graham's (CHA) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Graham (CHA) makes marginal contact with Russell (MIN) as he disengages from the contact during the inbound.
Russell (MIN) and Graham (CHA) engage and separate during the inbound.
Beasley (MIN) commits a take foul on Bridges (CHA).
Monk (CHA) maintains a legal guarding position during Hernangomez's (MIN) jump shot attempt.
